        "createdAt": 1778712000000,
        "updatedAt": 1778712000000,
        "output": {
          "status": "success",
          "text": "**The strongest case against is that this codifies sloppy review as the new normal.**\n\nThe PR-review failure mode is well-documented: when authors stop trusting AI output, they skim. When they trust it, they rubber-stamp. Neither produces good tests. You'll get tests that *look* comprehensive and silently rot.\n\nConcrete objections:\n\n1. **The tests will be locally plausible and globally wrong.** Sonnet doesn't know that the auth middleware in this codebase already handles 401s for you, so it'll write a 401 test that duplicates middleware coverage. You're inflating coverage metrics without adding signal.\n\n2. **The 25% feature-time figure is misleading.** Half of that quarter is engineers *thinking about the contract* while writing tests \u2014 catching design bugs before they ship. Skip that step and you'll catch them in production instead. The cost moves; it doesn't disappear.\n\n3. **A snippet library + Copilot rules captures 80% of the value at 10% of the risk.** You already have Copilot. The marginal improvement from a 3-week custom pipeline over \"better prompts + a `tests-for-handlers.md` rule file\" is real but not 3-week-engineering real.",
          "durationMs": 4900
        },
        "lastInputHash": "[[\"RFC: AI-written test suites\",\"## RFC: Let Claude write the test suite for new endpoints\\n\\n**Author:** platform-eng@  \\u00b7  **Status:** Draft  \\u00b7  **Decide by:** end of sprint\\n\\n### Current state\\n\\n- Every new HTTP handler ships with a hand-written test file (Vitest + supertest)\\n- Engineers spend ~25% of feature time writing tests\\n- Coverage hovers at 71%; the gaps are concentrated in error paths and edge cases\\n- Senior devs complain about \\\"happy path bias\\\" in junior-written tests\\n\\n### Proposal\\n\\nFor each new route, the PR includes an autogenerated `*.spec.ts` produced by Claude\\nSonnet given (a) the handler source, (b) the route's OpenAPI schema, and (c) a\\nproject-wide testing-style cheatsheet. Authors review and edit before merge.\\n\\n- **Estimated build:** 3 weeks (prompt, eval harness, CI integration)\\n- **Owner:** developer-experience team\\n- **Reversibility:** disable by env flag in 5 minutes; no DB or runtime coupling\\n\\n### Decision needed\\n\\nGreenlight the pilot for Q3, or invest the same eng-weeks in a hand-tuned snippet\\nlibrary + Copilot rules instead?\\n\"]]",
